{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<p>Since today is March 14 (or 3/14) here’s a small Silverlight App showing 3 expansions of Pi. With the slider you can control how many steps of the expansion you want to consider (With the maximum being 50). Equations are taken from <a href=\"http://www.math.hmc.edu/funfacts/ffiles/30001.1-3.shtml\">here</a> and <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Numerical_approximations_of_%CF%80\">here</a>. </p>\n <div id=\"silverlightControlHost\"><object data=\"data:application/x-silverlight-2,\" type=\"application/x-silverlight-2\" width=\"500\" height=\"300\"> \t\t  <param name=\"source\" value=\"/assets/piday/PiDaySL.xap\" /> \t\t  <param name=\"background\" value=\"white\" /> \t\t  <param name=\"minRuntimeVersion\" value=\"3.0.40818.0\" /> \t\t  <param name=\"autoUpgrade\" value=\"true\" /> \t\t  [  \t\t\t  ![Get Microsoft Silverlight](http://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/?LinkId=108181) \t\t  ](http://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/?LinkID=149156&amp;v=3.0.40818.0) \t    </object><iframe style=\"border-right-width: 0px; width: 0px; border-top-width: 0px; border-bottom-width: 0px; height: 0px; visibility: hidden; border-left-width: 0px\" id=\"_sl_historyFrame\"></iframe></div> \n<p>Happy Pi Day!</p>","frontmatter":{"date":"March 14, 2011","path":null,"title":"In honour of the Pi Day &ndash; Expansion Series in Silverlight","tags":["software-development","geekdom","mathematics","libs-and-frameworks"]}}},"pageContext":{"title":"In honour of the Pi Day &ndash; Expansion Series in Silverlight","previous":{"fields":{"slug":"/2011/02/27/thats-when-i-realized-my-incantation-of-the-automation-api-had-gone-wrong"},"frontmatter":{"title":"That's when I realized my incantation of the Automation API had gone wrong","tags":["dotnet","libs-and-frameworks"],"date":"2011/02/26"}},"next":{"fields":{"slug":"/2011/04/20/removing-some-of-datarows-ugliness-through-net-4-0s-dynamic"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Removing some of DataRow's ugliness through .NET 4.0’s dynamic